 But the Mia is not for everyone. I also heard stories about people whose faces just went backwards. 

00:01:02.140 --> 00:01:07.420
 I only have positive experiences, and my face only improved. 

00:01:07.600 --> 00:01:13.980
 I use the Clarasonic in combination with the Clinique Liquid Facial Soap, for combination / oily to oily skin. 

00:01:14.120 --> 00:01:17.680
 This is the first step in the Clinique step-by-step plan, which I use. 

00:01:17.680 --> 00:01:24.340
 If you do not know what the Clinique 3-step plan is, it is a cleanser, toner and cream, made especially for your skin type. 

00:01:24.420 --> 00:01:31.880
 There are four skin types. I'm number three, I don't know exactly what the others are, but if you have oily skin, number 3 is perfect for you. 

00:01:31.880 --> 00:01:36.040
 And this works well if you have pimples, or dry spots on your face. 

00:01:36.180 --> 00:01:44.680
 I like this because it contains aloe vera leaf juice, which is good for healing pimples or scars. 

00:01:44.740 --> 00:01:49.320
 On the other hand, it also contains sodium benzoate, which is irritating to the skin. Some suffer more from this than others. 

00:01:49.320 --> 00:01:51.314
 I personally only have positive experiences with this product. 

00:01:51.500 --> 00:01:58.360
 After cleaning, I use a toner, and I use the Clinique Clarifying Lotion. This is step three in the step-by-step plan. 

00:01:58.360 --> 00:02:12.440
 I'm not going to lie people, it dries out your skin. For some it is worse than others, but some had to accutane themselves through this. 

00:02:12.440 --> 00:02:18.240
 So I recommend that you first try the trial version before you buy a whole bottle. 

00:02:18.280 --> 00:02:24.120
 But even though it dries out skin, I still like it because it works together with the other products from the step-by-step plan. 

